<item>
            <title>[LU-15398] MR peers may put their own interfaces into peer recovery mode</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15398</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a MR peer has a MR peer entry for itself (can happen if manually created or discovery is run on itself for some reason), then it is possible for it to put its own interfaces into peer recovery. Problems with local interfaces should be handled via local NI recovery.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
